  "response": "Cannibals are individuals or groups of people who consume the flesh or internal organs of other human beings. This practice is known as **cannibalism**. Cannibalism can occur for various reasons, including cultural, ritualistic, survival, or pathological purposes. Historically, it has been documented in certain societies as part of warfare, religious ceremonies, or funerary rites. In extreme survival situations, such as famine or being stranded, cannibalism has been practiced out of necessity.\n\nWhile cannibalism is rare in modern societies, it continues to be a subject of fascination and horror in literature, media, and popular culture. It is important to note that cannibalism is widely considered taboo and is illegal in most countries. In some cases, it is associated with criminal behavior or mental health disorders.",
